editorialNotes.standard: With Party Pack 3 on Apple TV, we’re gonna need a bigger living room. Jackbox uses iPhones, iPads, and other devices as controllers, so everyone can play at once. It’s an easy and awesome way to get the gang together.

editorialNotes.standard: Austrian student Klemens Strasser studies computer science at the Technical University of Graz, and Elementary Minute is his first major development project. An absorbing quiz game, it gives you a minute to answer as many true/false questions as you can. If you prefer to take your time, you can try another mode that gives you four chances to get the right answer before the jig is up.

Ancient Egyptians loved cats, Metallica hasn’t played the Super Bowl, and the Ganges is India’s largest river—all our useless knowledge is now coming in handy thanks to Trivia Crack. This bite-sized trivia game is totally irresistible, whether we’re dominating our Facebook friends in classic mode, trouncing strangers in the 12-question challenge mode, or just sneaking in a game on our Apple Watch. With its cute characters, heaps of unlockable achievements, and a massive variety of questions, we simply can’t get enough.

editorialNotes.standard: This ingenious take on crossword puzzles challenges you to rearrange a square of letters to create words. With endless possibilities and limited clues to help, it’s a devilishly clever test of logic and vocabulary that you’ll love.
